cs.GT, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.MS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.GT (Game Theory): The paper discusses decision making and rationality, which are topics closely related to game theory. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper uses mathematical logic to define a qualitative ordering on nonstandard models of the real numbers. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a generalization of the principle of maximization of expected utility, which is a fundamental concept in AI decision making. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the properties of the generalized notion of rationality in different frameworks, which involves analyzing algorithms and data structures. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper uses mathematical software to study the properties of the generalized notion of rationality.
